<paragraph lastPageId="210" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia plumosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia plumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species and one of the few in the genus to have the abaxial leaf surface tan colored from the dense indument covering it. This characteristic leaf underside is shared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel, Almeda &amp; A. Estrada" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia dissitinervia" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dissitinervia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia dissitinervia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centrosperma" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centrosperma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia centrosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia incurva" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Donn. Sm." baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia oligocephala" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligocephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia oligocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In particular, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia plumosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia plumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Donn. Sm." baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia oligocephala" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligocephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia oligocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both of which occur in the same general area of northern Central America. The other species mentioned are endemic to southern Central America. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia plumosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">
<pageBreakToken pageId="210" pageNumber="211" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
plumosa
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the calyptrate calyx and short style with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but not with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Donn. Sm." baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia oligocephala" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligocephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Conostegia oligocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which lacks the calyptrate calyx and has an exserted style. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia plumosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Conostegia plumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of its evident calyptra appendices which are absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia xalapensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Conostegia xalapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
